main event: Mr. BYERS reported observing an unidentified flying object over St. Paul, Minnesota, at approximately 1900L on 24 November 1966.
interesting points: The object was a bright, round, silver-colored object that appeared to be 20-30 feet in diameter.
The object hovered in the sky for approximately 10-15 minutes without any visible means of propulsion.
The object made a sudden and rapid vertical ascent before disappearing from view.
Mr. BYERS was able to obtain a photograph of the object, which he submitted to the United States Air Force for analysis.
The report includes several grainy, black-and-white photographs that appear to show indistinct objects in the sky, possibly UFOs.
photographs: yes, the report includes several photographs
